Dorsal surfaces smooth, in adults with granules above sacrum and on tops of thighs. Ventral and lateral surfaces smooth. Postrictal and paracloacal tubercles not detected. Preaxillary surface with aspect of bulging glandular tissue (= postrictal bulge ). Tubercle on eyelid absent in preservative (Ethanol 70 %), but low and conspicuous in life (
ICN 55437
) (
Fig. 4
). A small cloacal sheath covering cloaca (see discussion in
Grant et al . 2006
).

One adult male (
ICN 55436
) has the dorsal surface of head and body olive-brown and a large irregular blackish spot on vertebral region. Broad blackish band on flanks. Ventrolateral flanks with a white ventrolateral stripe. Upper lip pearly white. Gular-chest region and lateral region of the belly blackened with white spots on axilar surface. Hind-limbs brown with black bands. Ventrolateral region on hind-limb near to groin and paracloacal marks bright yellow. Forelimbs cream.
